        Because it was not possible to extract data on quality
        of life (QOL), this issue was not addressed here. However,
        a recent systematic review by <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Bottomley et al</ENAMEX> [ <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">37</TIMEX> ]
        indicated that solid evidence about the effect of <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">EPO</ENAMEX> on
        this end point is lacking. We should also mention that the
        high cost of <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">EPO</ENAMEX> has deterred its widespread acceptance [ <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">5</NUMEX>
        ] and more studies using economic analysis should be done
